19th St Bay Beach
properties.google-review: 5/5: Great place to launch SUP or kayaks. Paid parking is right up against the beach for easy access & short distance to carry your craft. Shower stand allows for easy rinsing. Restroom facilities nearby at the playground. Easy paddling to circle Lido Island, head up into the Back Bay, or over to Balboa Island.

properties.name: Huntington State Beach
properties.google-review: 5/5: I love this beach, my first time visiting it was August of 2024. Then again just recently in September of 2024. The weather is wonderful, normally 65 to 80 degrees. The water IS very cold however once adjusted to it, it's simply spectacular. The waves are huge & great for surfers.

properties.name: Newport Municipal Beach
properties.google-review: 5/5: Newport is a really nice little town in the middle of big LA. It is quaint and beautiful. We enjoy strolling along here and also enjoyed dipping our toes in the Pacific Ocean. Whilst in LA this should really be on your to do list. New time we come we will plan to stay longer. It is also to be noted that it is very convenient (even with a big car) and has lots of restaurants & shops. Highly recommended!

properties.name: 10th St Beach
properties.google-review: 5/5: Excellent place, cozy and beautiful 😍 Good for a quick stop

properties.name: Dog Beach | Huntington Beach
properties.google-review: 5/5: Absolutely the most fun place for dogs to play in the water and on the beach. They easily make new friends...no leash required. Beach is very clean and dog owners are so nice! Convenient though limited parking. Need credit card to pay for parking at the kiosk.

properties.name: Bolsa Chica State Beach
properties.google-review: 5/5: Bolsa Chica in Huntington Beach is a perfect spot for bird watching and peaceful walks. If you love nature, you’ll never get bored—each visit offers a unique experience with different light reflections, stunning sunsets, and a quiet atmosphere. A must-visit for anyone who enjoys the beauty of the outdoors!
properties.adress: Bolsa Chica State Beach, California, USA

properties.name: Huntington City Beach
properties.google-review: 5/5: Catching sunset at Huntington Beach Pier was unreal. The sky lit up with these insane gold and pink colors that made the ocean look like something out of a painting. Walking along the pier, with the waves crashing below and surfers doing their thing was amazing to watch. Honestly, if you want to grab a bite and watch the sunset, try out HB Pier.

properties.name: Sunset Beach
properties.google-review: 5/5: In the 90s, there was a TV series called Sunset Beach, so when this location happened to be near our recent California stay, we knew paying it a visit was a must. It was a lovely short trip and the first time experiencing the Pacific Ocean and its prodigious waves. We enjoyed seeing the kiteboarders and the windsurfers while we took a walk down the beach. The beach was clean and fairly populated, and we had no problem finding parking.
